-- Deluxe Entertainment’s $475 Million Term Loan Rises in Trading
-- B y   M i c h a e l   A m a t o
-- 2011-12-22T21:37:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/deluxe-entertainment-s-475-million-term-loan-rises-in-trading.html
Deluxe Entertainment Services Group
Inc.’s $475 million term loan to refinance debt, rose in initial
trading.  The debt, which matures in June 2017, began trading at
96.38 cents on the dollar, according to data provider Markit
Group Ltd. The loan was sold to investors at 96 cents, Bloomberg
data show.  Credit Suisse Group AG arranged the financing for the Los
Angeles-based company, which is a unit of Ronald Perelman’s
MacAndrews & Forbes Holdings Inc., Bloomberg data show. The loan
pays interest at 6.5 percentage points more than the London
interbank offered rate, with a 1.5 percent floor on the
benchmark.  To contact the reporter on this story:
